-- Morgan Stanley Hires Bush White House’s Davis for Communications
-- B y   D o n a l   G r i f f i n
-- 2013-04-29T15:27:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-29/morgan-stanley-hires-bush-white-house-s-davis-for-communications.html
Morgan Stanley (MS)  hired Michele Davis,
who held communications roles at George W. Bush’s White House
and Henry Paulson’s Treasury Department, as global head of
corporate affairs.  Davis will join as a managing director, Chief Executive
Officer  James Gorman  and vice chairman Tom Nides wrote in a memo
to employees today. In her last government position, she helped
Paulson’s team during the credit crisis.  “Michele’s extensive experience will serve the firm well
as we communicate our strategic vision to stakeholders and
continue to build our franchise,” they wrote.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Donal Griffin in New York at 
